  - {fileID: 21300000, guid: fdbdd0ff85dd3204c9b9f0fa69f929c5, type: 3}
  - {fileID: 21300000, guid: 3cac5898a5d8df14fa2a9ad32eefb6ac, type: 3}
  - {fileID: 21300000, guid: 3693d742eae685840b96298eb37bdf22, type: 3}
  - {fileID: 21300000, guid: 918373e1cedc0ba41bb253af800ae76b, type: 3}
  lines:
  - A firefly's first memory is always the same.
  - A light slowly went out.
  - Lumi woke as the brightest of the year,
  - and played as if summer would never end.
  - Tonight the others seal their light into the seeds.
  - The ritual that lets them be reborn next spring.
  - Mine is too faint to do so.
  - But I know every turn of this park.
  - Tonight, I stay.
  lineClips:
  - {fileID: 8300000, guid: e4bfc0c6269704047bd074a47b91bcc9, type: 3}
  - {fileID: 8300000, guid: e6d7e7d059bc80a4b93cf3bc95d8f382, type: 3}
